data.description:
15374 LOWER TOWN CREEK RD OLDTOWN MD

Built in 2003, this like-new rancher is a super ownership opportunity right along Town Creek.  This could be your country home where you can enjoy all four seasons of the year or a recreational property when you want to getaway.  Home features include a living, dining, kitchen, family room with wood burning fireplace, master suite, two additional bedrooms and another full bath.  The large wrap deck overlooking the creek may be your favorite place to spend your time! 1792 finished square feet of living space, a full, unfinished basement for storage or finishing, and an attic.  The buyer of this property will have the opportunity to purchase deeded hunting and fishing rights on nearby 348 acres.  Green Ridge State Forest is also nearby.Town Creek is a 41.6 mile long tributary stream of the Potomac River.  The creek is formed from the confluence of Sweet Root Creek and Elk Lick Creek about a half mile south of Buchanan State Forest in Bedford County Pennsylvania.  Town Creek flows south along the base of Warrior Mountain in Allegany County Maryland.  It empties into the Potomac River about 4 miles east of Oldtown,  Maryland.  It is great for fishing, canoeing, kayaking, and there are some great swimming holes as well. 

Our agents are licensed in Maryland, Pennsylvania, and West Virginia.  Give us a call at 301-722-9292 to start working with a professional agent for your next property purchase.
